The paper discusses security threats in wireless sensor networks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The focus is on geo-sensor networks, which are a type of wireless sensor network used for environmental monitoring, so it is likely to also fall under the sub-category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The proposed framework involves load distribution and decision making, which could be categorized under distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The paper also mentions the use of anomaly detection and intrusion confirmation, which are common topics in systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the paper proposes a secure model for the geo-sensor network, which could be categorized under software engineering (cs.SE).
